  <bioghist id="aspace_a91ec750c4a481154ef0bbb617f1bc18">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Professor of geology.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_0cfa6556a772075e0c82a30f8e2b0187">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Papers include irrigation surveys of western states, 1883-1889; pictures of the Peary Arctic Expedition of 1896; diary of the expedition by B. Hoppin; scrapbook kept by Tarr as a Cornell professor; geology field books; notebooks of his son, Russel S. Tarr; diary kept on the Cornell Alaska Expedition, 1906; lectures on the geography of North America; notes on lab work in an experimental physiography course, 1907-1908; glass slides and negatives; and correspondence on Tarr's early years. Also, Geology Department records and reports kept by Tarr and his successors and a ledger of information on graduate students in the Geology Department.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_71e41f12d56e1ea702b352d2dd1879be">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Ralph Stockman Tarr papers, #14-15-92. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
